  "prompt": "How come America has cheaper branded clothes then European countries?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why branded clothes tend to be cheaper in the United States compared to European countries:\n\n1. Larger market size\n- The US has a bigger consumer market\n- Larger production volumes lead to lower manufacturing costs\n- More competitive retail environment\n\n2. Lower taxes\n- European countries often have higher import and sales taxes\n- VAT (Value Added Tax) in Europe is generally higher than sales tax in the US\n- These additional taxes increase final retail prices\n\n3. Domestic production\n- More clothing brands have manufacturing facilities in the US\n- Lower transportation and import costs\n- Closer proximity to production sites\n\n4. Retail strategy\n- American brands often use more aggressive pricing strategies\n- More frequent sales and discounts\n- Larger outlets and discount stores\n\n5. Lower labor costs\n- Manufacturing in countries like Mexico or Southeast Asia is cheaper\n- US brands can leverage lower production costs more effectively\n\n6. Different consumer culture\n- US consumers are more price-sensitive\n- More competitive retail market drives prices down\n- More discount shopping options\n\n7. Currency exchange rates\n- Favorable exchange rates can make US prices more attractive to international buyers\n\nThese factors combine to make branded clothing generally less expensive in the United States compared to European countries.",
